properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 12 at 10:48PM CST until February 13 at 10:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW AND WIND ALONG WITH MUCH COLDER TEMPERATURES OVERNIGHT...

.Hazardous travel will continue overnight as untreated roads,
bridges, parking lots and sidewalks will be snow or ice covered.

The combination of cold temperatures and winds will result in
wind chills as low as 20 below to 25 below zero over north
central and parts of central Wisconsin late tonight into Thursday
morning.

Motorists should anticipate hazardous travel conditions tonight,
especially in the Fox Valley and lakeshore areas. Anyone planning
outdoor activities should dress in layers and cover exposed skin
to avoid the risk of frostbite.

* WHAT...Bitterly cold wind chills expected. Wind chills as low
as 20 below to 25 below zero.

* WHERE...Portions of central, north central and northeast
Wisconsin.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 10 AM CST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...The cold wind chills could cause frostbite on exposed
skin within 30 minutes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Travel conditions will be locally
hazardous due to snow or ice covered roads, so motorists
should plan accordingly.
properties.instruction:
